{{EngvarB|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox company |name = Hyderabad Information Technology and Engineering Consultancy City |logo = MindSpace campus in Hyderabad, India.jpg |area_served = |key_people = |industry = Information Technology |products = |services = |revenue = |operating_income = |net_income = |caption = The VEGA Towers - HITEC City |foundation = |location_city = [[Rangareddy]] District, [[Hyderabad]], [[Telangana]] |location_country = [[India]] |homepage = {{URL|http://www.ltinfocity.com/}} |nickname= }} [[File:Cybertowers hyd.jpg|thumb|Cyber Towers in Hyderabad HITEC City]] [[File:L&Thyderabad.jpg|thumb|Cyber Gateway in Hyderabad HITEC City]] [[File:IlabsCentre.jpg|thumb|Ilabs Oval in Hyderabad]] [[File:The V- Twin Building view.jpg |thumb|'''V Twin Building campus in Hyderabad HITECH City''']] [[File:CyberPearl Madhapur Hyderabad.jpg|thumb|'''Cyber Pearl IT Park in HITECH City''']]
The '''Hyderabad Information Technology and Engineering Consultancy City''', abbreviated as '''HITEC City''', is an [[Information Technology]], [[Engineering]], [[Health informatics]], and [[Bioinformatics]] campus in the suburbs of [[Hyderabad]], [[Ranga Reddy district]], India. Located 15km² from the centre of Hyderabad, HITEC City lies within the '''Cyberabad''' Development Area, now part of the [[Hyderabad metropolitan region]].<ref name="Kennedy2013"/>
== History == HITEC City was launched in 1995 as a joint venture between [[Larsen & Toubro]] (L&T) and the Andhra Pradesh government.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Internet Society|authorlink1=Internet Society|title=OnTheInternet|date=1997|publisher=Internet Society|page=35|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=0a9TAAAAYAAJ|language=en}}</ref> The project outside the city limits when launched, included hubs in the suburbs of [[Madhapur]], [[Gachibowli]], [[Kondapur, Ranga Reddy|Kondapur]], [[Manikonda]], [[Nanakramguda]], [[Pocharam, Ranga Reddy district|Pocharam]], [[Uppal Kalan|Uppal]], [[Shamirpet]], and [[Shamshabad]]. The {{convert|151|acre|ha}} of land was contributed by the government.<ref>{{cite web|title=City Profiles, India Tier 1 Cities|url=https://www.cityinfoservices.com/downloads/CityReports-Tier1.pdf|page=6|publisher=Cityinfo Services Pvt Ltd|date=12 January 2014}}</ref> The Project is being developed through its Special Purpose Vehicle, L&T Hitech City Limited, a joint venture company of L&T Infocity Limited and the then [[Andhra Pradesh Industrial Infrastructure Corporation]] (APIIC). HITEC City has emerged as the symbolic heart of cosmopolitan Hyderabad.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/india-today-survey-on-best-cities-of-country-hyderabad/1/251324.html|title=Hyderabad: Colossal Gloss in City of Boom|website=Indiatoday.intoday.in|accessdate=20 October 2017}}</ref>
The Cyberabad Development Area (CDA) was established in 2001 to promote "the effective development of the areas around the HITEC City and surroundings". The CDA Master Plan was published that year by the Cyberabad Development Authority.<ref name="Kennedy2013">{{cite book|last1=Kennedy|first1=Loraine|title=The Politics of Economic Restructuring in India: Economic Governance and State Spatial Rescaling |date=2013 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=9781317937982 |page=128 |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=ZoliAgAAQBAJ|language=en}}</ref><ref name="AP-abstract">{{cite web|title=Municipal Administration & Urban Development Department – Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority – Approval of Metropolitan Development Plan-2031 for Hyderabad Metropolitan Region - Orders - Issued|url=https://www.hmda.gov.in/Gos/G.O.Ms.No.33,dt.24.1.2013%20(DMDP-2031).PDF|publisher=Government of Andhra Pradesh|page=2|date=24 January 2013}}</ref> The 52 km² zone, neighbouring the residential and commercial areas of [[Jubilee Hills]] and [[Banjara Hills]], lies mostly within [[Serilingampally]], 15km from the centre of Hyderabad. The Cyberabad Development Authority was dissolved in 2008, its functions merged into the [[Hyderabad Metropolitan Development Authority]].<ref name="AP-abstract"/>
